{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1711", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1711/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1711/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1711/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/datalad/datalad/issues/1711", "id": 249698521, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUyNDk2OTg1MjE=", "number": 1711, "title": "!datalad --help  in ipython with systemwide installed, goes to man pages -- rendering is screwed up", "user": {"login": "yarikoptic", "id": 39889, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODg5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39889?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic", "html_url": "https://github.com/yarikoptic", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2017-08-11T17:26:21Z", "updated_at": "2018-04-06T23:25:38Z", "closed_at": "2018-04-06T23:25:38Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "![rendering](http://www.onerussian.com/tmp/gkrellShoot_08-11-17_132239.png)\r\nI do not think it is our fault, since I could run e.g. `!man ls` or `!git commit --help` to get the same screw up.\r\n\r\nipython is \r\n```\r\nThe version of the notebook server is 4.0.6 and is running on:\r\n\r\nPython 3.5.3 | packaged by conda-forge | (default, Feb  9 2017, 14:37:12) \r\n[GCC 4.8.2 20140120 (Red Hat 4.8.2-15)]\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nit is a problem similar to the progressbars handling in ipython (#1541) -- we could only discover that we are under IPython session but cannot tell anything about frontend and its capabilities really.  E.g. terminal ipython would render our progressbars and manpages just fine, while web frontend would require custom progressbars and `--help-np` output.  It feels that we might want by default to assume safest default, which would be a mix of -- our broken-in-webfrontent progressbar + --help-np output. And then allow explicit specification of the mode (e.g. `datalad.set_ipython_frontend('web')`)\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "yarikoptic", "id": 39889, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5ODg5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39889?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic", "html_url": "https://github.com/yarikoptic", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yarikoptic/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1711/reactions